# 8.6 Filesystem MCP

---

## Purpose

The Filesystem MCP generates Markdown reports.

Example

```
AI_Germany_Report.md

Machine_Learning_USA.md

Technical_University_of_Munich.md
```

---

## Why Filesystem MCP?

Instead of returning only chat responses,

the project generates structured reports.

This demonstrates that AI agents can produce persistent artifacts rather than only conversational output.

---

## Communication

```
Local MCP

↓

STDIO
```

Execution

```bash
npx @modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem
```

---

## Responsibilities

Create Files

↓

Write Markdown

↓

Save Reports

↓

Return Success

---

## Internal Flow

```
Gemini

↓

Google ADK

↓

Filesystem MCP

↓

Node Process

↓

Markdown File

↓

Success

↓

Gemini
```

---

## Runtime Requirements

Unlike the Scholarship MCP,

Filesystem MCP is implemented as a Node.js package.

Therefore it requires

```
Node.js

npm

npx
```

This dependency became the most significant deployment challenge in the project.

---

## Before Docker

Local

```
Node Installed

↓

Filesystem MCP

↓

Success
```

Render Python Runtime

```
Node Missing

↓

Filesystem MCP

↓

Session Failure

↓

Worker Timeout
```

---

## After Docker

Docker Image

```
Python

+

Node

+

npm

+

npx
```

↓

Filesystem MCP

↓

Success

↓

Markdown Generated

Docker standardized the execution environment and resolved the runtime dependency issue.

---

## Report Storage

Local

```
project_root/reports/
```

Docker

```
/app/reports/
```

Important

Render containers are ephemeral.

The reports exist only while the container is running.

Future versions should store reports in:

- Amazon S3
- Google Cloud Storage
- Azure Blob Storage
- Render Persistent Disk

