# 8.8 Lessons Learned

The project demonstrated several important architectural principles.

### Different MCP servers can coexist.

A single AI agent successfully interacted with both Remote and Local MCP servers.

---

### Runtime dependencies matter.

Python-based MCP servers and Node.js-based MCP servers have different execution requirements.

Deployment environments must satisfy all required runtimes.

---

### MCP servers should have focused responsibilities.

Each server in this project performed one specialized task.

This modularity simplified testing, debugging, and future extensibility.

---

### Docker standardizes heterogeneous runtimes.

The Filesystem MCP issue highlighted the importance of containerization when combining tools built with different technologies.

